	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston SoCa.</placeName> <date>July 20. 1855</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Is. Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
				<p rend="indent(4)">Dear Sir&#8212;<sic>Inclosed</sic> I<lb/> send you the conclusion of the essay&#44; promised to you several months<lb/> ago.  Engagements of the most various nature&#44; amongst which those attend&#45;<lb/>ant upon <hi rend="underline">going to house&#45;keeping</hi> were not the least&#44;&#8212; have&#44; till now&#44;<lb/> prevented me from redeeming my promise.  I do it now&#44; and hope<lb/> you will excuse me for the long delay&#58; Better late than never.</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">Yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">most friendly &#38; respecting</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">Dr. M. Mayer</persName></p>
				<p>P. S. Would you&#44; perhaps&#44; have no objection to the publication of a<lb/> retrospective view at the history of the Jews of A. M. <date>5615</date>&#44;<lb/> as it is published every year in the German papers&#63;  The <date>September</date> number<lb/> of the Occident being to be published a few days <sic>befor</sic> <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; I<lb/> think&#44; such a sketch would not be taken amiss by your<lb/> readers.  If you wish to have it&#44; I am willing to write it&#44; but<lb/> then you would have to allow me some longer time than you usually<lb/> allow&#44; as I should wish to carry the history as far down as possible.<lb/>  Please let me know at once.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</p> 
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">Dr M Mayer</persName></p>
		</body>
